HEADWORD: Homophyly
<hw>Ho*moph"y*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Homo-</ets>
+ Gr. <?/ a clan.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>That form of homology
due to common ancestry (phylogenetic homology), in opposition to
<xex>homomorphy</xex>, to which genealogic basis is wanting.</def>
<rj><au>Haeckel.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

